author: jkaputin
msg: Added support for SOAP extensions to the BindingFault
component. This includes the ability to handle the
wsoap:code ext attribute as a 'union of xs:qname or
xs:token #any' and the wsoap:subcodes ext attribute as
a 'union of list of xs:qname or xs:token #any'.
Added behaviour to the initialization of Component
extensions in ComponentModelBuilder so that registered
extensions will only be instantiated if the related
extensions elements or attributes actually appear in the
WSDL or if the default rules for SOAP and HTTP apply, as
specified in WSDL 2.0 Part 2 Adjuncts.

author: jkaputin
msg: Added boolean query methods to AttributeExtensible and
ElementExtensible to check if an element contains any
extension attributes or extensions elements for a
specified extension namespace. These methods are used
to determine which of the registered Component model
extensions need to be instantiated when the Component
model is initialized by ComponentModelBuilder.
